# Upstream API keys for the travel-tools MCP server's tools.
#
# These belong to THIS service only — they are read by the MCP server and never
# reach any agent. Copy to mcp/travel-tools/.env (gitignored); scripts/bootstrap.sh
# sources it into a dedicated `travel-tools-secrets` Kubernetes Secret that only
# the travel-tools Deployment references. For standalone local dev, load it with
# Node's built-in flag: `npm run build && node --env-file=.env dist/index.js`.
#
#   cp mcp/travel-tools/.env.example mcp/travel-tools/.env   # then fill in + `make bootstrap`
#
# convert_currency uses Frankfurter (ECB rates) — no key, so nothing for it here.

# search_flights → Duffel Air. A TEST access token from https://app.duffel.com
# (Developers → Access tokens); read+write test scope is fine.
DUFFEL_API_KEY=

# search_hotels → LiteAPI. A free sandbox key from https://dashboard.liteapi.travel
# (instant, self-serve). Leave blank to run without hotels — flights + currency
# still work and the hotel tool reports that it isn't configured.
LITEAPI_KEY=
